15 the woman or child, as applicable, may be eligible to receive.
16 Existing law establishes certain rights for patients of medical facilities and
17 facilities for the dependent. (NRS 449A.100-449A.124) Section 2.6 of this bill
18 establishes certain rights of a parent or legal guardian of a newborn child who is
19 receiving care in a neonatal intensive care unit of a hospital. Section 2.2 of this bill
20 authorizes the suspension or revocation of the license of a hospital that fails to
21 honor such rights.
